Title : Morales Carrión Diplomatic and Foreign Relations School
Text : The '''Dr. Arturo Morales Carrión Diplomatic and Foreign Relations School''' ({{lang-es|Escuela Diplomática y de Relaciones Exteriores Dr. Arturo Morales Carrión|links=no}}) is the only [[List of schools of international relations in the United States|school of international relations]] in [[Puerto Rico]]. The school was created by [[Secretary of State of Puerto Rico]], [[David Bernier]], on November 19, 2013 in order to advance the academia of [[diplomacy]] and [[international relations]] on the island which is non-existent.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.pr.gov/agencias/estado/Pages/ED2.aspx |title=Rol de la Escuela |publisher=Pr.gov |date= |accessdate=2015-02-28}}</ref> The school honors the name of [[Arturo Morales Carrión]], is ascribed to the [[Department of State of Puerto Rico]], and does not confer any degrees as it is still in development.

